The paper deals with multimodal sentiment and emotion classification using video segments, which involves the domains of language, audio, and video. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses techniques to fuse modalities, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of video segments suggests the possibility of using computer vision techniques, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also presents a new architecture, which involves modeling inter-modal interactions, suggesting the possibility of using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with sentiment and emotion classification, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
